    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "The results of mixing angle measurement for \u03b7 \u2032 , \u03b7 mesons generated in charge exchange reactions with \u03c0 \u2212 and K \u2212 beams are preseneted. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "When the \u03b7 \u2032 , \u03b7 mesons are described in nonstrange(NS)strange(S) quark basis the \u03c0 \u2212 and K \u2212 beams allow to study |\u03b7q and |\u03b7s parts of the meson wave function. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The cross section ratio at t \u2032 = 0 (GeV/c) 2 in the \u03c0 \u2212 beam is R\u03c0(\u03b7 \u2032 /\u03b7) = 0.56 \u00b1 0.04 and result in mixing angle \u03c6P = (36.8 \u00b1 1.) o . ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "For K \u2212 beam the ratio is RK (\u03b7 \u2032 /\u03b7) = 1.30 \u00b1 0.16. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "It was found that gluonium content in \u03b7 \u2032 is sin 2 \u03c8G = 0.15 \u00b1 0.06. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The experiment was carried out with GAMS-4\u03c0 Setup.",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The investigation of the meson structure started during the second part of the last century, when in the native quark model frame the experimental consequence of the SU (3) broken symmetry had been measured. ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "In this model the physical states \u03b7 \u03b7 \u2032 are the linear combination of SU (3) singlet and nonet:",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "where",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "and \u03b8 P -the mixing angle in singlet-octet representation. ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "In nonstrange(NS)-strange(S) quark base",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "the mixing becomes",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "and the angles \u03b8 P and \u03c6 P are related through",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "But it is appear that the internal structure of the pseudoscalars is not so simple, and the outlined approach is simplified [1]. ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 124,
                    "end": 127,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The experimental properties of the \u03b7 \u2032 can be explained by assuming that there is a gluonium component in the meson wave function [2][3][4][5]. ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 130,
