        {
            "text": "where \u03c8 P is the \u03b7\u2212\u03b7 \u2032 mixing anlge and sin 2 \u03c8 G is the gluonium fraction in \u03b7 \u2032 . ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The KLOE result is sin 2 \u03c8 G = 0.12\u00b10.04. ",
            "section": "I. INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "* Electronic address: Vladimir.Samoylenko@ihep.ru As it was being understand in the process of the study of the meson structure, the accuracy of the mixing angle measurement can be improved if to prepare the known initial quark states ( |\u03b7 q or |\u03b7 s ), as in the B s , B d meson decays [7], ",
