        {
            "text": "IV. ",
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "CONCLUSION",
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The ratio of the differential cross sections at t \u2032 = 0 (GeV/c) 2 in the \u03c0 \u2212 beam equal R \u03c0 (\u03b7 \u2032 /\u03b7) = 0.56 \u00b1 0.04 and the mixing angle is \u03c6 P = (36.8 \u00b1 1.0) o in quark base. ",
            "section": "IV. CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "For the K \u2212 beam the ratio R K (\u03b7 \u2032 /\u03b7) = 1.30 \u00b1 0.16 corresponds the mixing angle \u03c6 P = (41.3 \u00b1 1.8) o which is incompatible with pion beam result at \u2248 2.5\u03c3 confidence level. ",
            "section": "IV. CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "We assume that the reason of this difference is the gluon content in \u03b7 \u2032 meson. ",
            "section": "IV. CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "Two angle mixing scheme with gluon mixing angle \u03c8 G result in gluon content sin 2 \u03c8 G = 0.15 \u00b1 0.06 for \u03b7 \u2032 meson.",
            "section": "IV. CONCLUSION",
            "paragraph_rank": 27,
